> Buckle up, because the power bowl just got a whole lot more powerful. Yep, this
> dish is a veritable one-bowl feast that's positively bursting with flavor. The
> base is savory, carrot-studded rice, and it's topped with pickled red cabbage,
> tender sautéed kale, curry-spiced crispy chickpeas, golden raisins, and a
> tangy curry-lemon dressing. It doesn't get much better than that.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}; dry thoroughly with #paper towels{}. Trim,
peel, and quarter @carrot{3%ounce} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick
pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Remove and discard any large stems from
@kale{4%ounce}; finely chop leaves. Place @golden raisins{1%ounce} in a
#small bowl{} with enough hot water to just cover.

Toss chickpeas on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon},
half the @curry powder{1/2%tablespoon} (you'll use more in the next step),
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until crispy, ~{18-20%minutes}. (It's natural for chickpeas to
pop a bit as they roast.)

While chickpeas roast, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a
#small pot{} over high heat. Add carrot and ¼ tsp curry powder (½ tsp for 4).
(You'll use the rest of the curry powder in the next step.) Cook, stirring, until
fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @water{1%cup} (1¾ cups for 4), @veggie stock
concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce
to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off
heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine juice from three lemon
wedges and @sugar{1%teaspoon} (six wedges and 2 tsp sugar for 4 servings); stir to
dissolve. Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and @water{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP
for 4); season with salt and pepper. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Set aside,
tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{6%tablespoon}, lemon zest, remaining
@curry powder{1/2%tablespoon}, and juice from remaining lemon. Season with salt
and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling
consistency.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
kale and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender,
~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Remove from
heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings)
and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with kale, pickled cabbage (draining first),
and chickpeas in separate sections. Drain and sprinkle raisins (roughly chopping
first if desired) over top. Drizzle with dressing and serve.